1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:02,120
The children love each other.

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,920
I won't accept a thief and a murderer's
daughter as a bride before going nuts.

3
00:00:08,200 --> 00:00:09,640
They made their decision.

4
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:11,320
I do not accept that decision.

5
00:00:11,400 --> 00:00:12,400
Enough!

6
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:14,680
Just because you do not approve...

7
00:00:14,960 --> 00:00:17,400
does not mean I will give up the woman I
love.

8
00:00:18,160 --> 00:00:19,959
If
Only you had declared your true identity...

9
00:00:19,960 --> 00:00:22,280
and why you are here.

10
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,080
Tell this to Ms. Mercan.

11
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:26,600
Let
us see if you can still hold her hand then.

12
00:00:26,920 --> 00:00:31,120
How will you send her father
to prison while holding her in your arms?

13
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,120
Will she not ask you why?

14
00:00:33,240 --> 00:00:34,640
Will she not question what you did?

15
00:00:34,680 --> 00:00:36,600
Mercan is my red line.

16
00:00:36,880 --> 00:00:40,079
If anyone tries to cross it...

17
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,560
they will face a different Ateş.

18
00:00:43,120 --> 00:00:47,080
Mercan and Ateş appeared
hand in hand and declared their love.

19
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:47,880
What?

20
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:51,960
I think you should forget Mercan now.

21
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,120
I am Haydar Yıldırım’s son.

22
00:00:54,600 --> 00:00:58,760
This man is either lying or he is a con
artist playing along with this woman’s games.

23
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:01,160
Burak...

24
00:01:02,280 --> 00:01:03,520
tell me the truth.

25
00:01:04,040 --> 00:01:05,800
Believe me, I am telling you the truth.

26
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,080
But if you do not believe me...

27
00:01:08,880 --> 00:01:11,120
You can look at the DNA report.

28
00:01:13,280 --> 00:01:14,360
He is telling the truth.

29
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:18,720
If you knew earlier, why didn't you say
anything? We could have taken precautions.

30
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,600
You should have taken
that precaution twenty years ago, Haydar.

31
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,320
A new incident, a new lie every time.

32
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:29,160
Dad, you were my hero.

33
00:01:30,720 --> 00:01:32,480
How could you betray us?

34
00:01:33,520 --> 00:01:39,480
We tried to work
with you, but this will not work.

35
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:41,600
I do not have time to waste, Aslı.

36
00:01:42,680 --> 00:01:44,560
Now you will tell me everything.

37
00:01:45,040 --> 00:01:47,040
Who is Ateş Karahan?

38
00:01:47,360 --> 00:01:49,320
Why did you meddle in our lives?

39
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,720
What do you want from the Yıldırım family?

40
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,080
Are you okay?

41
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,600
You have wrapped yourself in silence again.

42
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,040
Yes, I am fine.

43
00:03:06,320 --> 00:03:07,640
I was only thinking.

44
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,960
You were going to say something.

45
00:03:16,840 --> 00:03:18,640
There is a lot I want to say actually.

46
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:23,000
But now is not the time.

47
00:03:24,920 --> 00:03:25,920
Then when?

48
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:35,560
Not today, at least.

49
00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:46,800
I laugh at my own misery now.

50
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:52,080
I must have scared you
so much you were afraid to say anything.

51
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:55,961
You are trying
not to put too much pressure on me, right?

52
00:04:00,080 --> 00:04:01,440
What a family we are.

53
00:04:03,520 --> 00:04:04,520
My brother…

54
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:06,920
…killed a young girl and hid it.

55
00:04:08,240 --> 00:04:09,600
And went on with his life.

56
00:04:14,360 --> 00:04:15,360
Then my father…

57
00:04:16,080 --> 00:04:19,080
Rumors about the
dirty business my father was involved in…

58
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,000
He kidnapped you, tried to kill you.

59
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:30,360
And now…

60
00:04:31,320 --> 00:04:32,320
…Burak.

61
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,000
What do you think I am going through?

62
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,760
Is not all this strange?

63
00:04:44,440 --> 00:04:44,920
Or…

64
00:04:45,400 --> 00:04:47,880
…is
all this normal and am I the abnormal one?

65
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,000
You are abnormal.

66
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:54,920
For patience’s sake.

67
00:04:55,280 --> 00:04:56,640
You should look at yourself first.

68
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,160
What is wrong with me?

69
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:06,880
Say it.

70
00:05:08,440 --> 00:05:09,440
What is wrong with me?

71
00:05:12,640 --> 00:05:14,560
You are quite abnormal too.

72
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,360
Your arrival…

73
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,560
…entering our lives.

74
00:05:22,160 --> 00:05:23,479
About you…

75
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,600
…I still barely know anything, for example.

76
00:05:29,040 --> 00:05:30,920
And I love you like this.

77
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:32,440
Just as you are.

78
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:37,240
That makes me even more abnormal.

79
00:05:41,200 --> 00:05:42,960
I know nothing about him.

80
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,559
He is so fragile when it comes to the past.

81
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:48,040
I even hesitate to ask anything.

82
00:05:48,480 --> 00:05:50,200
At least not today.

83
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:58,440
You went through hard things in the past, I
know.

84
00:05:59,680 --> 00:06:01,200
But now there is today.

85
00:06:08,080 --> 00:06:09,480
Growing up without parents is hard.

86
00:06:11,880 --> 00:06:14,080
You have
no one to hold on to in good times or bad.

87
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,240
But I was lucky.

88
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,360
There was Mother Müzeyyen.

89
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:29,520
If it were
not for her, I might have been lost by now.

90
00:06:35,520 --> 00:06:36,720
Now I am here too.

91
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:40,080
You are my family.

92
00:06:50,320 --> 00:06:51,160
Well…

93
00:06:51,161 --> 00:06:53,039
…after what happened…

94
00:06:53,040 --> 00:06:55,680
…my head is really scattered.

95
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,040
I… need to work.

96
00:06:57,520 --> 00:06:58,920
I have not been able to focus much.

97
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:01,640
It is best if I go and work a bit.

98
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:03,200
It will clear my head.

99
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,360
Who is this Ateş anyway?

100
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,720
Why does he hide his past so much?

101
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,080
Why is there no trace of it?

102
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:42,960
Does not a
person have a single photo, a single story?

103
00:07:45,400 --> 00:07:47,000
As if the man fell from the sky.

104
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,600
Or as
if someone rewrote everything from scratch.

105
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:56,560
Now you will tell me everything.

106
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,840
Put that gun down.

107
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,640
Do not be ridiculous.

108
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:04,360
We both know perfectly
well you cannot shoot me.

109
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,080
Do not be so sure, Aslı.

110
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,000
Now answer my questions.

111
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:11,800
There is nothing to tell.

112
00:08:12,120 --> 00:08:13,120
He is Ateş.

113
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,720
Just the way he is.

114
00:08:14,960 --> 00:08:16,560
Handsome, rich, successful…

115
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,840
You will not glorify
Ateş to me anymore, Aslı.

116
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:25,080
Tell me, who is this Ateş Karahan?

117
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:30,279
So you will not talk, huh?

118
00:08:30,280 --> 00:08:31,320
Fine.

119
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,040
Then I will go to Ateş and tell him every
scheme you pulled behind his back.

120
00:08:38,720 --> 00:08:39,840
Go ahead, tell him.

121
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:45,040
I do not even care if I die.

122
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:47,000
It would be better, actually.

123
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,480
I would be free.

124
00:08:48,560 --> 00:08:49,800
Are you insane?

125
00:08:50,240 --> 00:08:51,240
Pull your hand away.

126
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,440
Why?

127
00:08:52,680 --> 00:08:55,000
Did you not pull the gun to kill me anyway?

128
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,320
What happened?

129
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,360
Do you not have the nerve?

130
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:03,600
Look, girl, pull your hand away.

131
00:09:04,320 --> 00:09:07,319
One wrong move and you
will be dead, hear me.

132
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:09,480
No one would ever find your body, pull your
hand away.

133
00:09:10,600 --> 00:09:12,600
Rather than seeing Ateş
and Mercan together…

134
00:09:13,680 --> 00:09:15,000
…I would rather die.

135
00:09:16,280 --> 00:09:18,439
If you truly want Mercan…

136
00:09:18,440 --> 00:09:20,040
…do not ever stand against me.

137
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:22,600
You cannot do anything without me.

138
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:27,160
I am the one closest to Ateş.

139
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:29,680
You will not find a better ally than me.

140
00:10:15,880 --> 00:10:19,080
I tried to explain, but
I was afraid you would pull away from me.

141
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:23,440
You
broke my heart, Malik. You broke it badly.

142
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:26,520
You always talk about love.

143
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,960
What about trust then?

144
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,480
Did you never trust me at all?

145
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:33,280
Whatever you say, you are right, Çiçek.

146
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,000
You are right, whatever you say.

147
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:37,160
I know you are hurt.

148
00:10:37,760 --> 00:10:39,760
I will
do whatever it takes for you to forgive me.

149
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:42,400
I would die right here if it would help.

150
00:10:56,680 --> 00:11:01,600
Come on,
Malik, turn this glass back to how it was.

151
00:11:02,400 --> 00:11:03,400
Can you?

152
00:11:04,280 --> 00:11:05,280
You cannot.

153
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,120
It will never be the same.

154
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,880
And I will
never be the same with you again.

155
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:14,520
Çiçek, my feelings for you are sincere.

156
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:18,080
I only
did not tell you about my family situation.

157
00:11:18,800 --> 00:11:22,200
Fine, you are right, but I do not
know… it should not be this much trouble.

158
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:24,320
It should not.

159
00:11:24,680 --> 00:11:25,680
It really should not.

160
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:28,120
Then why did you hide it from me, Malik?

161
00:11:28,600 --> 00:11:31,280
Or were you trying
to see if I was after your money?

162
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,640
No, of course not.

163
00:11:33,760 --> 00:11:35,720
Çiçek,
I told you, you know it was not like that.

164
00:11:37,840 --> 00:11:40,720
If I had said I was rich, I would not have
gotten that job…

165
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:44,560
…and I would not have been able
to get close to you, Çiçek. That is it.

166
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:53,279
I see how hurt and angry you are from your
eyes, I know.

167
00:11:53,280 --> 00:11:55,920
That is why
I will wait until you calm down.

168
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:57,480
I will not calm down, Malik.

169
00:11:58,080 --> 00:12:00,280
Do whatever you want.
I do not care, all right?

170
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,800
You did not trust me.

171
00:12:02,280 --> 00:12:04,200
You are being unfair to me now.

172
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,640
I explained it, you know the situation.

173
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:09,040
I told you, I explained everything.

174
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,080
Please.

175
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:16,600
You can accuse me as much as you want.

176
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:21,520
But no matter
what happens, no matter what we go through.

177
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:23,720
I will never give up on you.

178
00:12:26,360 --> 00:12:28,279
Because I…

179
00:12:28,280 --> 00:12:30,120
Because I love you very much.

180
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,160
All right?

181
00:13:09,800 --> 00:13:12,800
Did you come here to remember why
we came here in the first place?

182
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:16,080
What are you trying to say?

183
00:13:23,760 --> 00:13:25,800
Take that board down already.

184
00:13:33,640 --> 00:13:36,320
It has no meaning anymore.

185
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:43,280
Since
you have set off on a path with the girl…

186
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:47,880
…tear it all down.

187
00:13:51,040 --> 00:13:53,200
You swore revenge for years.

188
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,640
Your mother’s, father’s,
Eylül’s bones are aching in their graves.

189
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,280
Mother Müzeyyen!

190
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:01,560
Watch your words.

191
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,920
I saved you from death.

192
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,640
I took you off the streets.

193
00:14:08,080 --> 00:14:09,760
You promised me.

194
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:13,000
You
broke your promise for Haydar’s daughter.

195
00:14:19,840 --> 00:14:20,840
What is going on?

196
00:14:22,480 --> 00:14:25,640
Your voices can be heard outside. Maybe we
should watch our tone a bit?

197
00:14:26,440 --> 00:14:27,440
Who cares?

198
00:14:32,360 --> 00:14:33,360
What is going on?

199
00:14:50,280 --> 00:14:52,720
We see what you
have been through with Haydar’s daughter.

200
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:56,320
Naturally, my mother is worried as well.

201
00:14:56,920 --> 00:14:58,520
I have not given up on anything.

202
00:15:02,800 --> 00:15:03,800
All right.

203
00:15:04,000 --> 00:15:05,120
Okay, everyone calm down.

204
00:15:05,720 --> 00:15:08,720
I am tired of reminding you, but we are all
on the same boat.

205
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,680
We are fighting for the same purpose.

206
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,960
Let us keep
this in mind. It would be better.

207
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,840
Aslı.

208
00:15:19,440 --> 00:15:21,560
Why do you not go calm
Mother Müzeyyen down?

209
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:23,080
She seems to need you.

210
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:33,840
Ateş.

211
00:15:33,920 --> 00:15:34,920
Brother.

212
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:37,200
Things seem to be getting messy, huh?

213
00:15:39,720 --> 00:15:40,840
I know. I know.

214
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,480
I am at a dead end, Cemal.

215
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:46,360
You know Mother Müzeyyen.

216
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:48,160
When it comes to revenge…

217
00:15:48,161 --> 00:15:50,520
…and when
it is Haydar, this woman sees nothing else.

218
00:15:54,160 --> 00:15:55,160
Anyway.

219
00:15:55,320 --> 00:15:56,920
What did you do? Did you talk to Mercan?

220
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,200
No.

221
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,040
I am in such a difficult place right now.

222
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:12,200
I cannot dump
all this on her by telling her everything.

223
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,760
For the first time, I am afraid, Cemal.

224
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,400
Afraid of hurting Mercan…

225
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:23,960
…afraid of losing her.

226
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,400
I cannot take that risk.

227
00:16:31,160 --> 00:16:33,520
But Ateş, you have to choose a side now.

228
00:16:33,920 --> 00:16:35,720
Will you be Tahir, or will you be Ateş?

229
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,040
Make a decision already.

230
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:42,440
I do not even know who I am anymore.

231
00:16:43,840 --> 00:16:45,400
Who am I?

232
00:16:47,120 --> 00:16:48,400
Am I Tahir?

233
00:16:48,960 --> 00:16:50,440
Am I Ateş? Who am I?

234
00:16:52,680 --> 00:16:54,000
Who wants revenge?

235
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:57,280
Who wants
love? I do not know anymore, Cemal.

236
00:16:59,080 --> 00:17:00,320
I do not know anymore.

237
00:17:04,880 --> 00:17:06,120
I am lost now, Cemal.

238
00:17:09,640 --> 00:17:10,640
I am lost.

239
00:18:13,600 --> 00:18:15,920
Why did you want to talk to me?

240
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:18,920
Why did you call me back?

241
00:18:19,760 --> 00:18:21,480
Did you not reject me?

242
00:18:21,800 --> 00:18:22,800
What is next in line?

243
00:18:28,640 --> 00:18:31,999
Look… you suddenly showed up…

244
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,560
…said you were my son.

245
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:37,520
Who
can accept something like that immediately?

246
00:18:38,880 --> 00:18:41,440
My mother suddenly walked
out of my life, left me.

247
00:18:42,040 --> 00:18:43,520
I did not even know she was pregnant.

248
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:44,960
You did not know, huh?

249
00:18:46,880 --> 00:18:48,880
You always said you were in love with her.

250
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:51,560
Why did you never call her?

251
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,760
Why did you not ask for an explanation?

252
00:18:56,520 --> 00:18:59,320
She said
she was in love with someone else and left.

253
00:19:00,760 --> 00:19:03,640
My mother never loved anyone but you.

254
00:19:04,200 --> 00:19:05,800
She never let anyone else into her life.

255
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,079
Then why
would she hide something like this from me?

256
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:14,360
If I had known she was pregnant…

257
00:19:14,760 --> 00:19:15,760
Your wife, Nermin…

258
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:24,480
…when she learned my mother was pregnant…

259
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,760
…threatened her with me.

260
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:31,319
Either you leave…

261
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:33,440
…or I
will kill the child in your womb, she said.

262
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:37,120
My mother had no choice but to leave.

263
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:39,880
Nermin?

264
00:19:41,600 --> 00:19:44,200
Before my mother died,
she told me everything.

265
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:33,600
I wanted us to have a drink together.

266
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,440
You did well.

267
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:51,160
Even the coffee I
drink with you tastes different.

268
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,120
I feel the same.

269
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,880
Are you okay?

270
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:14,280
As much as possible.

271
00:21:19,240 --> 00:21:20,800
No matter how angry I get…

272
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:24,760
They are still my parents.

273
00:21:26,600 --> 00:21:28,040
Sometimes my mind drifts to them.

274
00:21:30,840 --> 00:21:33,800
I used to
come and watch my father work in this room.

275
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:36,600
I would help him.

276
00:21:37,560 --> 00:21:39,080
He liked it too.

277
00:21:40,560 --> 00:21:42,280
My mother would come and complain about us.

278
00:21:43,640 --> 00:21:44,679
According to her…

279
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:46,720
…girls should always wear pink.

280
00:21:47,600 --> 00:21:49,120
They should have pink rooms.

281
00:21:49,200 --> 00:21:50,800
They should wear pink jewelry.

282
00:21:51,880 --> 00:21:53,880
Ateş, would you believe it?

283
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,280
At one point, I truly hated pink.

284
00:22:03,400 --> 00:22:04,840
They raised me in this mansion…

285
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,320
…protecting me from all evil.

286
00:22:15,960 --> 00:22:18,800
But lovelessness and neglect are something
else.

287
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,600
Lovelessness is something no one can carry.

288
00:22:27,240 --> 00:22:28,920
Now that I think about it…

289
00:22:29,920 --> 00:22:33,680
…they really tried to
turn us into themselves.

290
00:22:34,920 --> 00:22:38,720
They never truly cared
about Mercan or Murat.

291
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:48,560
I lost my family at a young age.

292
00:23:00,080 --> 00:23:01,080
We were not rich.

293
00:23:03,920 --> 00:23:06,840
But I always knew they truly loved me.

294
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:10,440
Because they made me feel it.

295
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,880
This is the first time
you are talking about your family.

296
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,440
Tell me more.

297
00:23:22,640 --> 00:23:24,040
If only I could tell you.

298
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:36,680
They were simple people.

299
00:23:38,520 --> 00:23:39,760
Husband and wife, both working.

300
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,640
The last thing they did was drop us off at
school.

301
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:57,560
Then one day they left and never came back.

302
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:09,399
You know how that last image stays in your
mind…

303
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,680
…I always remember them waving at me.

304
00:24:37,960 --> 00:24:38,960
You said “us.”

305
00:24:44,320 --> 00:24:45,320
My sibling.

306
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:47,800
You had a sibling?

307
00:24:50,760 --> 00:24:52,160
Eylül is my sibling.

308
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,640
I am Tahir.

309
00:24:59,040 --> 00:25:00,040
She died too.

310
00:25:05,600 --> 00:25:06,440
I…

311
00:25:06,441 --> 00:25:08,560
…am truly sorry.

312
00:25:09,080 --> 00:25:11,160
So talking about this hurts you.

313
00:25:12,360 --> 00:25:14,480
I am very
sorry, let us close the subject right away.

314
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:16,040
It is fine.

315
00:25:18,840 --> 00:25:21,120
We had an ordinary life, but we were happy.

316
00:25:31,840 --> 00:25:32,920
Until they…

317
00:25:34,240 --> 00:25:35,800
…were taken from me.

318
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,840
Until they died.

319
00:25:50,600 --> 00:25:52,919
How beautiful it is…

320
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:56,160
…to talk about one’s family like this.

321
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:01,279
Sometimes I think…

322
00:26:01,280 --> 00:26:03,800
…our situation was so different.

323
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:07,240
We mistook authority for love.

324
00:26:09,520 --> 00:26:11,279
Maybe…

325
00:26:11,280 --> 00:26:15,800
…my brother went down the
wrong paths to fill that void in his life.

326
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:20,120
He
Always tried to earn my father’s approval.

327
00:26:22,600 --> 00:26:25,200
But he never received it, not even once.

328
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,400
Everything is completely tangled now.

329
00:26:35,040 --> 00:26:36,200
It is hard for my mother too.

330
00:26:37,360 --> 00:26:39,119
She lost her own son, but…

331
00:26:39,120 --> 00:26:41,440
…another
son of my father suddenly appeared.

332
00:26:44,840 --> 00:26:49,080
For a woman, learning
she was cheated on, deceived…

333
00:26:51,000 --> 00:26:53,920
…and then continuing her life knowing it.

334
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,520
What am I even saying?

335
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:04,400
Everything is piling up.

336
00:27:04,920 --> 00:27:06,960
No one could plan this much chaos.

337
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:20,320
If you were not here, I would have lost my
mind.

338
00:27:27,880 --> 00:27:29,599
You would get through anything…

339
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,080
…even without me.

340
00:27:32,800 --> 00:27:34,600
Never belittle yourself.

341
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:49,840
I know you are very tired today.

342
00:27:50,080 --> 00:27:52,240
We rode bikes, we did target practice.

343
00:27:52,760 --> 00:27:54,640
But I have one more surprise for
you tonight.

344
00:27:55,640 --> 00:27:56,640
Do not worry.

345
00:27:57,040 --> 00:27:58,600
It is not something that will tire you.

346
00:27:59,640 --> 00:28:00,640
What surprise?

347
00:28:01,320 --> 00:28:02,760
It is a surprise after all.

348
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:04,800
If I tell you, what meaning would it have?

349
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,920
If you
smile at me like that, I will do anything.

350
00:28:19,640 --> 00:28:22,480
But I will get spoiled
too, just so you know.

351
00:28:22,720 --> 00:28:24,720
And I will always expect it.

352
00:28:27,280 --> 00:28:28,320
You can always be spoiled.

353
00:28:28,880 --> 00:28:30,560
Because you deserve to be spoiled.

354
00:28:33,360 --> 00:28:34,400
Thank you.

355
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:41,320
At least give me a hint.

356
00:28:41,960 --> 00:28:42,960
No.

357
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:57,160
What kind of surprise is it, I wonder?

358
00:29:14,640 --> 00:29:17,119
Did you threaten Nurgül
with killing the baby in her womb

359
00:29:17,120 --> 00:29:18,640
and force her to leave, Nermin?

360
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:20,200
I did no such thing.

361
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,640
Do not lie!

362
00:29:22,080 --> 00:29:23,720
You threatened her and scared her.

363
00:29:24,680 --> 00:29:25,760
Enough already!

364
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:28,200
Are you questioning me about your mistress
now?

365
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:31,800
Do you have no shame asking
your wife about the mistress who ran away?

366
00:29:32,720 --> 00:29:33,840
What a disgrace this is.

367
00:29:34,280 --> 00:29:35,440
Do not drive me crazy, woman.

368
00:29:36,560 --> 00:29:39,040
I lived for years without knowing about my
son because of you.

369
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:41,840
You had one son.

370
00:29:42,760 --> 00:29:44,000
And he is under the ground.

371
00:29:45,240 --> 00:29:46,360
You did not protect my son.

372
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,400
You did not even care about his death.

373
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:53,320
Now you complain to me
because you cannot reach your son?

374
00:29:56,320 --> 00:29:58,120
What would
you have done if you knew, Haydar?

375
00:29:59,360 --> 00:30:00,800
Would you have taken responsibility?

376
00:30:03,120 --> 00:30:06,760
No matter what you
say, you cannot cover up the evil you did.

377
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,440
Well, well, well.

378
00:30:11,440 --> 00:30:14,800
So fate had it that I would receive
a lesson in virtue from Haydar Yıldırım.

379
00:30:17,560 --> 00:30:19,880
If it was evil, it was evil. Do you object?

380
00:30:21,840 --> 00:30:23,959
If your dear Nurgül truly loved you…

381
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,960
…she would not have run
away without looking back.

382
00:30:27,760 --> 00:30:30,079
I stayed and fought.

383
00:30:30,080 --> 00:30:31,600
But she ran.

384
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,760
If only she had stayed and fought.

385
00:30:33,920 --> 00:30:35,840
You threatened to kill her child.

386
00:30:38,520 --> 00:30:40,960
She was brave enough to have an affair with
her married boss…

387
00:30:41,200 --> 00:30:43,920
…but ran away
because of a few words from me, is that it?

388
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:46,920
Do not fool yourself, Haydar.

389
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:49,040
She ran away.

390
00:30:49,720 --> 00:30:53,040
Because she did not want
to raise her child with a lowlife like you.

391
00:30:56,600 --> 00:30:58,840
I wish I had packed up and run away too.

392
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:02,600
At least my son would be alive now.

393
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,760
Girl,
take that photo down, someone will see it.

394
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:41,760
This photo will be very useful to me.

395
00:31:44,120 --> 00:31:45,680
All right, do not look at me like that.

396
00:31:47,480 --> 00:31:49,520
We will keep it as a souvenir photo now.

397
00:31:50,360 --> 00:31:51,960
Revenge turned out to be a lie anyway.

398
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:56,840
I told you many times.

399
00:31:57,760 --> 00:31:58,800
Accept it, mother.

400
00:31:59,280 --> 00:32:01,120
You underestimated Mercan.

401
00:32:16,160 --> 00:32:19,040
Every time I see that man, I remember what
he did.

402
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:20,600
I lose my mind.

403
00:32:23,760 --> 00:32:26,799
Just as I took your
son’s life without getting my hands bloody…

404
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:28,880
…I should
have eliminated his daughter the same way.

405
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,200
Get well soon.

406
00:32:30,760 --> 00:32:31,760
What is done is done.

407
00:32:32,360 --> 00:32:33,800
I am full of your empty words.

408
00:32:35,280 --> 00:32:39,520
Whatever I do, I need
to do it without turning Ateş against me.

409
00:32:41,600 --> 00:32:42,880
So what will you do, mother?

410
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:45,880
I do not know.

411
00:32:46,680 --> 00:32:47,840
Ateş is a smart man.

412
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,200
But he is emotional.

413
00:32:53,120 --> 00:32:55,320
He does not forget kindness done to him.

414
00:32:56,640 --> 00:32:58,680
By using what I did for him…

415
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:01,240
…I will work my way around him.

416
00:33:03,800 --> 00:33:05,560
I will neither give up on revenge…

417
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:08,800
…nor let that murderer’s
daughter enjoy this fortune.

418
00:33:13,280 --> 00:33:14,600
This has dragged on too long.

419
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:35,760
Zehra, what happened?

420
00:33:37,880 --> 00:33:38,880
Berat.

421
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:41,960
I
Called off the engagement ceremony, Berat.

422
00:33:45,280 --> 00:33:47,560
Everything is too chaotic.

423
00:33:49,720 --> 00:33:51,240
Everyone has their own troubles.

424
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:53,240
The mansion is a mess, your house too.

425
00:33:57,560 --> 00:33:59,640
It is just a signature in the end.

426
00:33:59,760 --> 00:34:01,760
There is no need
for all this fuss, in my opinion.

427
00:34:09,840 --> 00:34:11,560
You do not need anyone anymore.

428
00:34:12,480 --> 00:34:14,320
All right? Not even that witch Müzeyyen.

429
00:34:16,640 --> 00:34:18,080
From now on, I am your family.

430
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:21,520
There is no you and me.

431
00:34:23,080 --> 00:34:24,080
There is us.

432
00:34:26,160 --> 00:34:27,280
Really?

433
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:30,520
Really?

434
00:34:35,960 --> 00:34:37,400
Do not be sad.

435
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,080
Wipe your tears.

436
00:34:40,360 --> 00:34:43,680
Do not dwell
too much on this marriage issue, all right?

437
00:34:44,680 --> 00:34:46,400
We will get married soon anyway.

438
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,560
All right? From now on, your family is me.

439
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:51,440
Your surname will be Güneş.

440
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:53,640
Zehra Güneş.

441
00:34:54,160 --> 00:34:55,160
All right?

442
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:57,079
No one will be able to stop us from now on.

443
00:34:57,080 --> 00:34:58,920
We will work hard.

444
00:34:59,240 --> 00:35:00,560
We will build our own life.

445
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:03,960
And then we will owe nothing to anyone.

446
00:35:06,560 --> 00:35:07,560
Berat.

447
00:35:08,480 --> 00:35:11,520
They say one should stay
with the person who values them.

448
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:14,840
That is a very true saying.

449
00:35:16,480 --> 00:35:17,560
Very true, right?

450
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:19,120
Very true, right?

451
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:21,160
Berat!

452
00:35:21,480 --> 00:35:23,120
What is it?

453
00:35:24,080 --> 00:35:26,760
When I get excited, things happen suddenly.

454
00:35:27,080 --> 00:35:28,200
Did it hurt?

455
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,320
It did not, you silly thing.

456
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,999
When I do things like this…

457
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:36,880
…my finger got
caught since the earring was big, I guess.

458
00:35:37,120 --> 00:35:40,360
But if you do this every
time you get excited, I am in trouble.

459
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:43,760
Something happened. Sorry, I got excited.

460
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,360
It will not happen again.

461
00:36:00,280 --> 00:36:02,600
You said
surprise, that really got me tense.

462
00:36:07,200 --> 00:36:08,720
It is something like this.

463
00:36:09,320 --> 00:36:10,720
What should I do?

464
00:36:16,560 --> 00:36:17,840
This does not feel right.

465
00:36:19,040 --> 00:36:20,720
Should I do something more colorful?

466
00:36:20,920 --> 00:36:22,240
Maybe two colors.

467
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,640
No.

468
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:40,040
It should be simpler, I think.

469
00:36:46,080 --> 00:36:47,080
I cannot decide.

470
00:36:56,160 --> 00:36:57,160
Well…

471
00:36:57,161 --> 00:36:58,561
I was preparing a surprise for you.

472
00:37:00,040 --> 00:37:01,880
What kind of surprise was it?

473
00:37:03,240 --> 00:37:05,159
When you prepare a surprise for me…

474
00:37:05,160 --> 00:37:06,720
…I did not want to survive it.

475
00:37:08,440 --> 00:37:11,600
I also wanted to thank you for being by my
side.

476
00:37:17,520 --> 00:37:19,000
I found a frame in the storage.

477
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,280
For our photo.

478
00:37:23,120 --> 00:37:24,720
Our photo already had a frame.

479
00:37:26,160 --> 00:37:27,720
But this was going to be my effort.

480
00:37:29,840 --> 00:37:31,080
You ruined the whole surprise.

481
00:37:32,960 --> 00:37:35,600
Since you are
here anyway, come on, give me your opinion.

482
00:37:37,360 --> 00:37:39,560
But it is not clear like this.

483
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,320
How so?

484
00:37:43,120 --> 00:37:44,640
That one looks nice.

485
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:57,800
Let me see.

486
00:37:58,040 --> 00:37:58,840
What did you do?

487
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:01,040
The color could be lighter.

488
00:38:11,720 --> 00:38:13,160
Lighter, you say?

489
00:38:15,800 --> 00:38:16,800
Here, look.

490
00:38:17,280 --> 00:38:18,600
This is quite light, for example.

491
00:38:19,440 --> 00:38:21,440
It suits you quite well too. It brightened
you up.

492
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:23,280
So it suits me? Then…

493
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:24,320
Do not.

494
00:38:24,600 --> 00:38:25,640
So you liked it.

495
00:38:26,080 --> 00:38:27,120
So you liked it.

496
00:38:37,160 --> 00:38:39,040
So you liked it.

497
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:49,280
I love you so much I felt like hugging you.

498
00:38:54,560 --> 00:38:57,680
Honestly, Ateş, I should probably go now.

499
00:39:10,400 --> 00:39:13,040
I think it would be better if I left.

500
00:39:17,560 --> 00:39:18,680
We embarrassed ourselves.

501
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:22,160
Come on, let us go to the room.

502
00:39:23,600 --> 00:39:24,960
Is there anyone outside?

503
00:39:25,960 --> 00:39:27,760
Whether there is or not.

504
00:39:28,440 --> 00:39:29,440
Who cares?

505
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:38,200
Let us go
and wash these paints off before they dry.

506
00:39:39,040 --> 00:39:41,360
You should have thought before misbehaving.

507
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:42,880
Come on.

508
00:40:11,840 --> 00:40:13,200
What is it, Zehra?

509
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,040
You seem quite pleased.

510
00:40:15,480 --> 00:40:18,040
Whose
life did you ruin this time to be so happy?

511
00:40:23,800 --> 00:40:25,159
Or rather…

512
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:27,600
I thought you would be in mourning.

513
00:40:28,640 --> 00:40:30,079
When you realized Malik was rich…

514
00:40:30,080 --> 00:40:32,560
…I thought your world would collapse.

515
00:40:34,720 --> 00:40:36,440
Did the big fish get away, Zehra?

516
00:40:37,600 --> 00:40:38,800
Were you not upset at all?

517
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:44,960
Malik does not matter to me at all, Çiçek.

518
00:40:47,160 --> 00:40:49,080
I was only interested in him to annoy you.

519
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:53,080
Though I am still annoyed with you…

520
00:40:55,040 --> 00:40:57,320
I felt nothing for him, you know.

521
00:40:59,160 --> 00:41:01,080
I acted that way just
so you would not be happy.

522
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,640
You are still lying.

523
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:08,320
Think whatever you want, sweetheart.

524
00:41:09,760 --> 00:41:12,239
Besides, I am not the one who lost the big
fish.

525
00:41:12,240 --> 00:41:13,240
You are.

526
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:16,560
There is tea if you want some.

527
00:42:02,760 --> 00:42:03,880
What is going on?

528
00:42:05,760 --> 00:42:06,760
Quiet.

529
00:42:08,920 --> 00:42:09,920
Why?

530
00:42:13,680 --> 00:42:15,440
Trust me.

531
00:42:16,080 --> 00:42:17,080
Surprise.

532
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:20,280
It smells like fresh popcorn too.

533
00:42:21,560 --> 00:42:22,120
Do you like it?

534
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:23,560
I love it.

535
00:42:24,760 --> 00:42:27,400
Then you can open your eyes.

536
00:42:46,440 --> 00:42:47,520
It is beautiful.

537
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:50,480
Which movie will we watch?

538
00:42:51,480 --> 00:42:54,080
Of course, our unfinished children’s movie.

539
00:42:58,800 --> 00:42:59,800
I am so moved.

540
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:02,400
Did the paint come off?

541
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,000
It did, yes.

542
00:43:04,920 --> 00:43:07,720
But yours did not
come off completely, right here.

543
00:43:22,680 --> 00:43:24,560
There is no poster this time, I guess.

544
00:43:26,520 --> 00:43:27,880
I knew you would bring this up.

545
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,520
I could not resist taking a jab.

546
00:43:31,800 --> 00:43:34,720
You ruined everything
that night out of jealousy.

547
00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:37,480
All right, I was jealous, happy now?

548
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:39,080
Very jealous.

549
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:42,480
What was the need? You had prepared such a
beautiful night.

550
00:43:42,680 --> 00:43:44,960
Then you tore everything apart.

551
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:47,360
My Mercan.

552
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:52,120
My beautiful face, my sweet mermaid.

553
00:43:55,960 --> 00:43:57,320
Shall we watch our movie now?

554
00:43:58,880 --> 00:43:59,880
Let us.

555
00:44:00,560 --> 00:44:02,520
I was very sad it was left unfinished.

556
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,000
It will not be unfinished anymore.

557
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:11,720
Nothing will be left unfinished.

558
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:21,680
Come on.

559
00:44:27,000 --> 00:44:28,040
Here you go.

560
00:44:50,760 --> 00:44:52,080
Let us start the movie.

561
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,360
Çiçek!

562
00:45:39,920 --> 00:45:43,360
Çiçek, I will wait here
until you forgive me.

563
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:50,840
The idiot will freeze in the cold.

564
00:47:02,160 --> 00:47:04,840
The movie is over
there, Ateş. You are looking the wrong way.

565
00:47:07,920 --> 00:47:10,920
No, I am looking the right way.

566
00:47:12,960 --> 00:47:14,600
I am watching the movie of my life.

567
00:47:16,160 --> 00:47:17,480
You are my story.

568
00:47:30,800 --> 00:47:32,680
You have not eaten any of your popcorn.

569
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:34,720
Look, only mine is finished.

570
00:47:38,680 --> 00:47:40,120
Should I get you something to drink?

571
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:42,120
Or wait, I will get you something to eat.

572
00:47:49,160 --> 00:47:51,160
You talk too much during movies.

573
00:47:59,200 --> 00:48:00,520
Good to know.

574
00:48:33,160 --> 00:48:35,960
Did it hurt a lot? I am sorry.

575
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:41,480
If you want, you can always bite me.

576
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:11,800
This time we managed to watch all of it.

577
00:49:14,720 --> 00:49:16,720
We said
children’s movie, it turned out emotional.

578
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:19,240
But at least it ended happily.

579
00:49:20,280 --> 00:49:22,040
I cannot handle sad endings these days.

580
00:49:23,040 --> 00:49:26,760
A story ending
sadly does not mean it is not worth loving.

581
00:49:27,560 --> 00:49:30,760
Well, yes, but I like happy endings.

582
00:49:32,720 --> 00:49:38,480
I hope our story lasts a lifetime and ends
happily too.

583
00:49:48,200 --> 00:49:50,240
No matter what we go through…

584
00:49:51,480 --> 00:49:53,840
…never forget that I love you, all right?

585
00:49:55,680 --> 00:49:58,120
Let us never lose each other.

586
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:07,240
Never.

587
00:50:08,200 --> 00:50:09,320
Every moment is precious.

588
00:50:11,080 --> 00:50:15,920
The more time I
spend with you, the more attached I become.

589
00:50:17,080 --> 00:50:19,320
I do not feel like leaving.

590
00:50:23,160 --> 00:50:25,080
You are always on my mind.

591
00:50:35,000 --> 00:50:36,720
I do not want to lose you.

592
00:51:30,200 --> 00:51:31,840
Good morning.

593
00:51:32,920 --> 00:51:33,920
Good morning.

594
00:51:38,120 --> 00:51:41,600
Did you
not sleep at all? Your eyes are bloodshot.

595
00:51:43,560 --> 00:51:45,520
I woke up a bit early.

596
00:51:46,320 --> 00:51:48,000
I did not want to disturb you.

597
00:51:51,720 --> 00:51:54,600
Last night I saw the two of us in my dream.

598
00:51:57,360 --> 00:51:58,440
How did you see us?

599
00:51:59,400 --> 00:52:01,200
You should say Insallah first.

600
00:52:02,640 --> 00:52:04,280
All right, Insallah.

601
00:52:08,840 --> 00:52:13,360
We were running hand in hand by the sea. We
were very happy.

602
00:52:15,560 --> 00:52:20,479
Then we went into the sea. I saw a huge key
in the water.

603
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:23,960
I bent down to take it, but you did not let
me.

604
00:52:25,120 --> 00:52:28,400
Then a huge wave came. It was enormous.

605
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:31,040
It felt very real too.

606
00:52:31,800 --> 00:52:34,200
Anyway. Thank God I woke up right away.

607
00:52:35,360 --> 00:52:36,360
It was just a dream.

608
00:52:37,720 --> 00:52:39,320
Are you not coming to the company today?

609
00:52:40,680 --> 00:52:41,800
Of course I am.

610
00:52:43,160 --> 00:52:45,200
Working always does me good, you know that.

611
00:52:46,640 --> 00:52:48,200
Why did you ask? Should I not come?

612
00:52:49,000 --> 00:52:50,680
No, maybe you would not.

613
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:53,720
I thought you might want to miss me.

614
00:52:54,880 --> 00:52:56,920
Are you tired of always being side by side
with me?

615
00:52:57,080 --> 00:52:59,680
Never. Are you?

616
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:02,040
Impossible.

617
00:53:06,360 --> 00:53:07,760
Let me wash my face and hands.

618
00:53:18,040 --> 00:53:19,040
Ateş!

619
00:53:24,200 --> 00:53:25,600
I like saying your name.

620
00:53:30,120 --> 00:53:31,680
But I was going to go in.

621
00:53:31,800 --> 00:53:33,080
But you could not.

622
00:53:34,560 --> 00:53:36,240
You trickster.

623
00:54:09,160 --> 00:54:10,240
Now that is something else.

624
00:54:15,520 --> 00:54:16,520
What are you doing?

625
00:54:18,880 --> 00:54:20,896
I watched a movie last
night and got carried away by it.

626
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:22,440
I am checking its summary again.

627
00:54:24,440 --> 00:54:25,440
I do not want to.

628
00:54:26,120 --> 00:54:28,119
Come on,
pull up a chair and let us watch together.

629
00:54:28,120 --> 00:54:29,120
It is a very good movie.

630
00:54:33,600 --> 00:54:34,600
Have you seen it?

631
00:54:42,360 --> 00:54:44,440
Are you okay? You seem down.

632
00:54:47,920 --> 00:54:49,640
You seem down, Ms. Zahide.

633
00:54:49,760 --> 00:54:51,840
I cannot keep talking
like this formally anymore.

634
00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:53,920
I cannot build any closeness with you.

635
00:54:59,320 --> 00:55:01,040
Have you noticed?

636
00:55:01,760 --> 00:55:03,040
Burak is nowhere around.

637
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:06,000
Maybe he has work.

638
00:55:10,520 --> 00:55:11,600
Demet is not around either.

639
00:55:12,280 --> 00:55:13,800
Maybe they went somewhere together.

640
00:55:16,160 --> 00:55:17,160
No.

641
00:55:17,840 --> 00:55:20,640
It is strange they have
not shown up for two days without notice.

642
00:55:21,280 --> 00:55:22,560
I have a bad feeling.

643
00:55:25,120 --> 00:55:27,640
Let me call and see what is going on.

644
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:34,840
He is not answering.

645
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:38,960
Something is clearly
going on with them, it will come out soon.

646
00:55:39,800 --> 00:55:41,840
Insallah nothing bad has happened.

647
00:55:43,600 --> 00:55:44,600
Insallah.

648
00:55:47,560 --> 00:55:48,560
Go on.

649
00:55:52,880 --> 00:55:56,480
What should I say,
the woman has nothing else to do.

650
00:56:35,600 --> 00:56:38,240
She really did not leave…

651
00:56:39,640 --> 00:56:41,360
Oh Malik.

652
00:58:03,080 --> 00:58:04,560
I will bring it right away.

653
00:58:19,520 --> 00:58:21,640
Did you make breakfast for me?

654
00:58:22,480 --> 00:58:23,480
Yes.

655
00:58:31,200 --> 00:58:35,480
Be careful, it is hot, I just made it.

656
00:58:40,600 --> 00:58:42,480
It turned out great, thank you.

657
00:58:45,040 --> 00:58:49,280
I did not make it though. Sister
Binnaz prepared it and froze it.

658
00:58:49,960 --> 00:58:51,160
So I took the easy way.

659
00:58:53,160 --> 00:58:55,960
You have really improved at reheating ready
meals.

660
00:58:57,960 --> 00:58:59,960
Of course. I do it well.

661
00:59:03,080 --> 00:59:04,360
I will teach you.

662
00:59:05,120 --> 00:59:06,120
We will do it together.

663
00:59:06,600 --> 00:59:09,080
Will you eat with the same appetite when I
cook, I wonder?

664
00:59:11,960 --> 00:59:14,880
I would eat poison from these hands.

665
00:59:17,800 --> 00:59:18,800
Oh.

666
00:59:20,520 --> 00:59:22,440
You have seemed down for days.

667
00:59:23,120 --> 00:59:24,600
You have barely eaten properly.

668
00:59:25,120 --> 00:59:27,560
I wanted you to at least
have a nice breakfast.

669
00:59:28,400 --> 00:59:29,400
Come on, let us sit.

670
00:59:29,560 --> 00:59:30,560
Come on.

671
00:59:36,480 --> 00:59:37,520
Thank you.

672
00:59:55,440 --> 00:59:57,200
Which dishes do you like the most?

673
01:00:00,000 --> 01:00:02,400
I was never picky about food.

674
01:00:04,160 --> 01:00:07,960
Once I learn, I will know what you like.

675
01:00:12,880 --> 01:00:16,000
Maybe I should rethink cooking altogether.

676
01:00:17,320 --> 01:00:18,320
Shame on you.

677
01:00:26,360 --> 01:00:27,920
Let it be love if it is with you.

678
01:00:34,560 --> 01:00:36,720
There are many things we do not know about
each other.

679
01:00:37,360 --> 01:00:39,640
But we have a long time to learn them.

680
01:00:46,880 --> 01:00:48,360
When will we leave?

681
01:00:49,960 --> 01:00:51,000
In a bit.

682
01:00:51,520 --> 01:00:54,320
But I have
a small thing to take care of in the study.

683
01:00:54,920 --> 01:00:56,136
It will not even take ten minutes.

684
01:00:56,160 --> 01:00:57,160
Will you wait for me?

685
01:01:01,280 --> 01:01:03,600
I would wait a lifetime for you.

686
01:01:10,520 --> 01:01:11,520
Come a little closer.

687
01:01:11,720 --> 01:01:12,320
What happened?

688
01:01:12,560 --> 01:01:13,560
Come closer.

689
01:01:17,520 --> 01:01:18,880
You do not need to wait that long.

690
01:01:26,960 --> 01:01:29,040
Come on, you are not eating the pastry.

691
01:02:07,680 --> 01:02:08,680
Çiçek.

692
01:02:10,440 --> 01:02:12,680
What is it, girl, where are you going with
that blanket?

693
01:02:19,600 --> 01:02:20,760
Is he still here?

694
01:02:22,720 --> 01:02:24,320
What is he still doing here?

695
01:02:24,440 --> 01:02:26,240
Brother, please, for God’s sake.

696
01:02:27,920 --> 01:02:29,640
Berat, stay out of it.

697
01:02:31,360 --> 01:02:34,160
Mom, step aside, let me talk.

698
01:02:34,520 --> 01:02:35,680
Son, I said do not interfere.

699
01:02:38,520 --> 01:02:40,680
I will handle it, all right?

700
01:02:40,720 --> 01:02:42,200
I will talk to him and send him away.

701
01:02:45,760 --> 01:02:47,680
Come on… go inside.

702
01:02:49,920 --> 01:02:50,920
Go on.

703
01:03:07,320 --> 01:03:08,320
Malik.

704
01:03:10,200 --> 01:03:11,680
Malik, get up.

705
01:03:16,800 --> 01:03:18,680
Have you lost your mind?

706
01:03:18,720 --> 01:03:20,560
Do you wait outside like this in the cold?

707
01:03:20,680 --> 01:03:22,040
Malik.

708
01:03:24,280 --> 01:03:25,280
Malik.

709
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:27,000
Malik, get up.

710
01:03:28,080 --> 01:03:29,080
Malik.

711
01:03:33,200 --> 01:03:34,200
Malik.

712
01:03:35,640 --> 01:03:36,680
Malik.

713
01:03:37,840 --> 01:03:38,920
Malik.

714
01:03:39,320 --> 01:03:40,320
Malik, wake up.

715
01:03:40,880 --> 01:03:41,880
Malik.

716
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:45,800
Oh my God, what happened?

717
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:46,960
Malik.

718
01:03:47,960 --> 01:03:48,960
Oh no.

719
01:03:50,120 --> 01:03:51,359
You are burning up.

720
01:03:51,360 --> 01:03:53,240
Oh no.

721
01:03:53,680 --> 01:03:54,680
Malik.

722
01:03:56,440 --> 01:03:57,440
Malik.

723
01:04:17,600 --> 01:04:19,040
Brother.

724
01:04:22,720 --> 01:04:23,720
What is with that face?

725
01:04:24,640 --> 01:04:27,160
Look, there is a nice toast, eat some. You
have not touched it.

726
01:04:30,840 --> 01:04:31,840
Are you okay?

727
01:04:33,400 --> 01:04:34,400
I am fine.

728
01:04:35,080 --> 01:04:36,080
Just a bit sleepless.

729
01:04:37,880 --> 01:04:40,560
That
face is not from lack of sleep, I know it.

730
01:04:42,000 --> 01:04:43,840
That useless
boy is still on your mind, right?

731
01:04:47,640 --> 01:04:49,040
Look at the sneaky one.

732
01:04:49,240 --> 01:04:51,600
He has not said
a single word since he came to the company.

733
01:04:52,400 --> 01:04:54,360
And on
top of that, he suddenly found a job here.

734
01:04:55,480 --> 01:04:56,480
Look, Demet…

735
01:04:57,440 --> 01:04:59,320
That boy is dangerous. Stay away from him.

736
01:05:00,440 --> 01:05:01,440
Look, brother.

737
01:05:02,040 --> 01:05:03,200
What he did affected me too.

738
01:05:04,840 --> 01:05:06,040
I accept it…
He broke my trust.

739
01:05:08,000 --> 01:05:10,000
And I cannot continue with someone I do not
trust.

740
01:05:11,520 --> 01:05:13,920
There was
nothing definite between us anyway.

741
01:05:15,800 --> 01:05:19,440
But judging people so easily is not right.

742
01:05:20,240 --> 01:05:21,400
One should try to understand.

743
01:05:22,040 --> 01:05:23,880
He made a mistake, I know that too.

744
01:05:25,200 --> 01:05:28,160
Maybe he did not feel ready to tell.

745
01:05:32,800 --> 01:05:35,600
Maybe if he did not care
about Uncle Haydar, he would have left.

746
01:05:36,040 --> 01:05:38,400
He came here just to understand what
kind of person he was.

747
01:05:40,320 --> 01:05:41,680
He was not ready.

748
01:05:43,160 --> 01:05:45,560
He can
tell those family stories to someone else.

749
01:05:48,520 --> 01:05:52,080
That fraud sneaked into
the company to learn about Haydar’s wealth.

750
01:05:54,240 --> 01:05:57,760
What wealth, brother?
Everything Haydar owns is mortgaged.

751
01:05:57,920 --> 01:05:59,520
Demet, do not huff at me.

752
01:06:00,520 --> 01:06:03,640
I do not buy that poor
orphan talk, all right?

753
01:06:06,440 --> 01:06:07,560
I have a lot of work.

754
01:06:09,680 --> 01:06:11,000
Enjoy your meal.

755
01:06:11,240 --> 01:06:13,040
Demet, sit down. Demet.

756
01:06:24,520 --> 01:06:27,320
We will learn who you
really are too, Mr. Burak.

757
01:06:52,160 --> 01:06:55,960
It is time to learn the truth about
Ateş, Ms. Mercan.

758
01:06:58,000 --> 01:07:01,160
Let us see if you will still be
able to have breakfast so cheerfully then.

759
01:07:46,640 --> 01:07:47,920
Do not let your coffee get cold.

760
01:07:48,440 --> 01:07:49,440
All right.

761
01:07:55,520 --> 01:07:57,240
I already have a very quick thing to do.

762
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:29,920
I will go check on Cemal.

763
01:08:30,960 --> 01:08:34,240
Okay.
Take him some pastry too. Let none be left.

764
01:08:46,600 --> 01:08:47,600
Ateş?

765
01:08:51,560 --> 01:08:52,560
Yes, my dear?

766
01:08:53,320 --> 01:08:54,560
What is it? Is there a problem?
